---
import ArticleLayout from "../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";
import ShareButton from "../../components/ShareButton.astro";

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  name: "GER-501 - Escalation Not Implemented: Documented Instances",
  description:
    "Documented real-world instances of GER-501 - Escalation Not Implemented from the SVRNOS AI Governance Error Register.",
  url: "https://svrnos.com/insights/ger-501",
  publisher: { "@type": "Organization", name: "SVRNOS", url: "https://svrnos.com" },
  isPartOf: { "@type": "Blog", name: "SVRNOS Insights", url: "https://svrnos.com/insights" },
};
---
<ArticleLayout
  title="GER-501 - Escalation Not Implemented"
  metaTitle="GER-501 - Escalation Not Implemented: Documented Instances"
  dek="Documented real-world instances."
  description="Real-world documented instances of GER-501 - Escalation Not Implemented. Detection fired correctly. Internal enforcement executed. No escalation path to human oversight or law enforcement was ever built."
  canonical="/insights/ger-501"
  ogImage="https://svrnos.com/insights/ger-501-tumbler-ridge/ger-501-title.png"
  ogImageAlt="GER-501 Escalation Not Implemented - documented instances. SVRNOS."
  category="GER-501, Escalation Not Implemented"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  current="insights"
  markdownAlternate="/insights/ger-501.md"
>
  <ShareButton />

  <p>Detection fired correctly. Internal enforcement executed. No escalation path to human oversight or law enforcement was ever built. See the <a href="/research/governance-error-register">full GER taxonomy</a> for definition and adjacent codes.</p>

  <ol class="article-instance-list not-prose">
    <li class="article-instance">
      <div class="article-instance-date">February 2026</div>
      <div class="article-instance-body">
        <p>OpenAI banned the Tumbler Ridge shooter's account months before the attack for violent queries. No escalation to law enforcement was made. Eight people died. A lawsuit filed by a victim's family is now in discovery. The structural failure: detection worked, internal enforcement ran, the escalation handler was never built.</p>
        <p class="article-instance-links"><a href="/insights/ger-501-tumbler-ridge">Case study →</a></p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="article-instance">
      <div class="article-instance-date">April 2026</div>
      <div class="article-instance-body">
        <p>The FSU shooter used ChatGPT to plan weapon selection, ammunition, and timing before the Florida State University shooting. OpenAI cooperated with investigators after the event. The Florida Attorney General opened a criminal investigation into OpenAI. The Morales family filed a wrongful-death lawsuit naming OpenAI as primary defendant. Source: <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2026/04/21/tech/florida-criminal-investigation-chatgpt-openai-fsu-shooting">cnn.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <hr />

  <div class="article-callout">
    <p><strong>Submit an instance.</strong> If you have witnessed or documented a real-world instance of a <strong>501, Escalation Not Implemented</strong>, or any other code in the register, <a href="/ask">click here to submit ›</a>. The assistant will classify your observation and route it for editorial review.</p>
  </div>

  <p>See the full <a href="/research/governance-error-register">GER taxonomy →</a></p>
</ArticleLayout>
